Zero shot audio classification using LAION’s CLAP

[1]:

from transformers.utils import logging
logging.set_verbosity_error()

[ ]:

# Building pipeline
from transformers import pipeline

zero_shot_classifier = pipeline(
    task="zero-shot-audio-classification",
    model="laion/clap-htsat-unfused"
)

[3]:

# Create zero shot labels | these goes into underlying text encoder
candidate_labels = ["Sound of a crying baby", "Sound of gunshot", "Sound of dog"]

[9]:

# load audio | model expects 48KHz Sampled Audio | output is scores distributed among labels | max score = 1
import librosa
from IPython.display import Audio as IPythonAudio

y, sr = librosa.load('1-187207-A-20.wav', sr=48000)

display(IPythonAudio(y, rate=sr))
zero_shot_classifier(y, candidate_labels=candidate_labels)

[9]:

[{'score': 0.9893468022346497, 'label': 'Sound of a crying baby'},
 {'score': 0.010021555237472057, 'label': 'Sound of dog'},
 {'score': 0.0006316996295936406, 'label': 'Sound of gunshot'}]

[14]:

# audio contains both gunshot & speech | but model gave importance only to gunshot
candidate_labels = ["Sound of a crying baby", "Sound of gunshot", "Sound of dog", "Sound of speech"]

y, sr = librosa.load('Y-inB65exXFU.wav', sr=48000)
display(IPythonAudio(y, rate=sr))
zero_shot_classifier(y, candidate_labels=candidate_labels)
